n film and television director and producer.\nTed Emery served in the Royal Australian Navy during the Vietnam War. After returning to Australia, he joined the ABC in Melbourne, Australia, and in time became a director and producer for the weekly ABC music program, Countdown.\nHe continued to work as an assistant director at the ABC on such programs as Power Without Glory, before moving into directing comedy series. He has worked consistently as a director, writer and producer of a number of Australian comedy television series and films, including Fast Forward, Full Frontal and Kath and Kim.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T17:15:22.134211+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 5244, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ted_Emery"}], "uuid": "aff97294-d3db-4b52-a975-9fcb5ae372f8", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "29520", "external_references": [{"id": 26430, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q28839849"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-06T01:42:33.842748+10:00"}, {"id": 22659, "name": "Prima Film", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2250375, "title": "Rififi = Du Rififi chez les hommes", "work_id": 93314, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 772347, "title": "The Little Mermaid", "work_id": 80525, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T17:10:02.370328+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "bc53024a-b190-44a7-8237-767d9c06e2ff", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "11639", "external_references": [{"id": 33083, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121144136"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-06T00:14:07.310054+10:00"}, {"id": 22656, "name": "Marilyn Fox"